'''''Star Wars Insider'' 41''' is the forty-first issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in [[December]] [[1998]].

==Contents==
===Features===
*"[[Terence Stamp: Stamp of Approval]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>The veteran British actor tells the ''Insider''{{'s}} [[Scott Chernoff]] about the highlights of his career, including stints in the ''Superman'' movies and his upcoming role as Supreme Chancellor [[Finis Valorum]] in ''Star Wars'': Episode I.</small>
*"[[Ewan McGregor: Portrait of the Jedi as a Young Man]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>Ewan McGregor grew up watching the ''Star Wars'' movies, but he never guessed he'd be stepping into the robe of Sir [[Alec Guinness]] as the young [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]]. The star of ''Trainspotting'' tells the ''Insider'' how it feels to be a Jedi.</small>
*"[[Retracing Bantha Tracks|Retracing ''Bantha Tracks'']]"
*:<small>Long before the ''Star Wars Insider'', there was ''Bantha Tracks'', the original ''Star Wars'' Fan Club newsletter. Kevin Fitzpatrick takes a fond look back at the first official ''Star Wars'' quarterly, and the early days of ''Star Wars'' fandom.</small>
*"[[The Evolution of Star Wars: Exploring the Lost Cut|The Evolution of ''Star Wars'': Exploring the Lost Cut]]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>He's rediscovered the [[Tunisia]]n locations for [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] and pulled back the curtain on the lost [[Anchorhead/Legends|Anchorhead]] scenes from ''A New Hope''. Now Dr. [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]] shares his latest discovery—a whole other version of ''Star Wars''.</small>

